Envi OData Public API 1.0 API Reference

This page contains description of Envi public OData API. It includes all public end-points as well as description of parameters and models used. You can use this page for testing and prototyping purposes.

API Reference

Name Type Required Comment
AddressID string optional Get or set the address ID value
OrganizationID string optional Get or set the organization ID value
OrganizationNO string optional Get or set the organization ID value
OrganizationName string optional Get or set the name of the organization
AddressNo string optional Get or set the address NO value
AddressName string optional Get or set the name of the address
AddressTypeID integer optional Get or set the address type ID
AddressType string optional Get or set the type of the address
FacilityID string optional Get or set the facility ID value
FacilityNO string optional Get or set the facility NO value
FacilityName string optional Get or set the name of the facility
AddressDescription string otional Get or set the description of the address
Address1 string optional Get or set the first address
Address2 string optional Get or set the second address
City string optional Get or set the city
State string optional Get or set the state
Zip string optional Get or set the zip
Country string optional Get or set the Country
ContactName string optional Get or set the name of the contact
ContactEmail string optional Get or set the email value
Phone string optional Get or set the phone value
PhoneExt string optional Get or set the phone extension value
Fax string optional Get or set the fax value
IsDefaultAddress boolean optional Get or set a value indication where this address is default
ActiveStatus boolean optional Get or set the active status of address
DateCreated string optional Get the date of creating the address
CreatedBy string optional Get the creator ID of the address
CreatedByName string optional Get the name of the address creator
LastUpdated string optional Get the date of last updating
LastUpdatedBy string optional Get the ID of last updating
LastUpdatedByName string optional Get the name of the last updater
API Endpoint
https://api-demo.envi.net
Schemes: http, https
Version: v1

Authentication

Authentication

POST /oauth2/token

Returns JWT token. Use this token with every action as required parameter for request header. To log into specified organization enter the organization Id in an appropriate parameter.

grant_type: string password
in formData

Grant Type of the auth request. Should be set to 'password'.

client_id: string 099153c2625149bc8ecb3e85e03f0022
in formData

Id of the client performing auth request.

username: string
in formData

Enter your User Name here.

password: string
in formData

Enter your Password here.

organizationId: string
in formData

Enter organization Id to log into not default organization.

200 OK
OAuthTokenResponse

undefined

400 Bad Request
OAuthErrorResponse

An error occurred during the authorization process.

400 (invalid_client_ID)

Provided client ID is invalid.

400 (invalid_grant)

Grant Type is invalid.

400 (maintenance)

Application is currently down for maintenance. It will be back as soon as possible.

400 (network restriction)

You cannot log in from the current network. Contact your application administrator.

400 (invalid cred.)

Provided password or login is incorrect or was mistyped.

400 (no role)

This account does not have any preconfigured role. Contact your application administrator.

400 (no org.)

No default organization is associated with this account. Contact your application administrator.

400 (locked)

This account has been locked. Check your email or contact your administrator to unlock it.

400 (no active role)

This account does not have any active role. Contact your application administrator.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "access_token": "string",
  "token_type": "string",
  "expires_in": "integer",
  "refresh_token": "string"
}
Response Example (400 Bad Request) 
{
  "error": "string",
  "error_description": "string"
}

Addresses

Addresses

Get list of addresses

GET /odata/Addresses

Returns paged list of the existing addresses within logged organization. You can filter the results by the strict match using $filter parameter â€“ entity eq â€˜stringâ€™. Or filter the results by the partial match using $filter=contains parameter â€“ contains(entity, â€˜stringâ€™). This endpoint does not support logical operators (and/or) for data filtering.

api-version: string 1.0
in header

The requested API version

$search: string
in query

Picks the value in all possible fields.

$filter: string
in query

Filters the results, based on a Boolean condition.

$orderby: string
in query

Sorts the results.

$top: string
in query

Returns only the first n results.

$skip: string
in query

Skips the first n results.

Authorization: string Bearer access_token
in header

Specify type of the token (bearer), and then insert the access_token, which was obtained during authentication.

200 OK
PageResult[Address]

OK

400 Bad Request

Incorrect input data or organization Id does not match with organization Id user is logged in.

401 Unauthorized

Incorrect specified access_token or access_token got expired.

403 Forbidden

User doesnâ€™t have appropriate privileges.

500 Internal Server Error

Server encountered with an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.

Response Content-Types: application/json, application/xml
